<$fill $name="body">

!! Adding help pages from your plugin

# Create `.tid` files under `your-plugin/llm-help/`
# Tag each with `$:/tags/rimir/llm-help/page`
# Set `llm-help-path` and `llm-help-description` fields
# The pages are discovered automatically when the plugin is installed

!! Restart rules

* Help page tiddlers (`.tid` files): ''no restart needed'' — they are shadow tiddlers read from the wiki store
* The `functions.tid` and `tool.tid` are also shadow tiddlers — ''no restart needed'' for content changes
* Changes to `settings.tid` (UI): ''no restart needed''

!! Testing help pages

# Start the wiki server
# Open Settings > LLM Help to browse the help tree
# Verify your pages appear at the expected paths
# Check that dynamic content renders correctly
# Test the `llm_help` tool in a chat session

!! Conventions

* Keep help content concise and LLM-readable — avoid complex wikitext formatting
* Use `$text` and `$list` widgets for dynamic content (they work in the tool executor's fakeDocument)
* Don't use `$reveal` or DOM-dependent widgets in help page content
* Use `$importvariables` to pull in functions from other plugins when needed
* Put shared procedures in a separate macro tiddler (like `type-info-macro.tid`)

</$fill>
</$transclude>
